Welcome to Camp Dan and Phil, a one week camp for all nerds in the Phandom that don’t like going outside!
Join our discord!
Header & icon by @infinitylester

summary: Camp Dan and Phil: Camper Signups
title: Camp Dan and Phil: Camper Signups
body:
kids, it’s finally time to sign up for campdnp!! the admins are ready, and we’re super hyped for you all to participate! 

what are you on about? 
campdnp is a week of activities, some of which may have to do with dan and phil, that you complete with a tent we put you in with other campers. obviously, everyone who signs up will be from the phandom. you’ll have the opportunity to meet new people while having tons of fun doing stuff like playing games, doing “arts and crafts”, and solving a murder mystery!

cool! hit me with the details! 
this summer’s camp will be from june 17-june 23! if you’re not going to be active the entire time, that’s okay, but we’d like you to be able to contribute a little bit to your tent if you’re going to sign up. the form should be pretty self-explanatory, but if you have any questions don’t hesitate to send us an ask! 

that’s awesome! how do i sign up?

you can sign up by filling out the form linked below! signups close on the 9th of june, 8pm BST.

i have another question?

feel free to send us an ask or scroll through our answered tag to see if your question has already been answered :)

SIGN UP HERE!

body:
Phanfic Events Spring Fic Reveal

Hello everyone! We’re ready to reveal the fics for the Spring Fic Exchange!

blog.name: phanfictioncatalogue
blog.title: phanfiction catalogue
blog.description:
mobile users, click here!

please refer to our FAQ first.

Our goal is to create an alphabetized library of every phanfiction in the phandom. Besides that, we compile masterlists of different genres that are scheduled for posting every few days, and help find fics that have been mislocated.

title: Fics Written In 2013 Masterlist
body:
Bloodlight - the-butt-llama

Summary: Dan tells Phil to take a ‘short cut’ home, leading him to end up with a lifetime issue.

(Co)dependency - thespianhowell

Summary: It’s not that Dan can’t cope on his own, it’s just that it’s a lot easier when he doesn’t have to.

Confessions - walruslovechild

Summary: Dan comes from a strict religious family.

Counting Stars - definitelythor

Summary: Phil bunks off school and smokes too much, and Dan’s a bit infatuated with him. It doesn’t take long to figure out that Phil’s just a dorky guy who likes stars and wants people to think hes cool.

Double Take - amazingdanielhowell

Summary: Dan and Phil meet their pornstar doubles.

Ghost Of A Good Thing (ao3) - SpacedOut

Summary: Dan and Phil hadn’t planned on Tesco exploding, it just kind of happened.

Hard to Breathe - studeye

Summary: This is basically a consensual gang bang centered on Dan, involving Phil, Benjamin Cook, Chris (Crabstickz), Jack Harries and Charlieskies.

It’s Not The Same Without You - cuddlephan

Summary: Phil arrives home from Florida and gives Dan a pleasant surprise after he’s been alone all week ;)

Midnight Magic - youtubers-for-all

Summary: Dan receives a letter the night of New Year’s Eve from a “secret admirer”, and he may just end up with a night better than he could ever have wished for.

Outdoor Adventures - the-butt-llama

Summary: Dan and Phil go camping in a tent.

Resistance - amazingdanielhowell

Summary: Dan moved up to Manchester after his already successful parents got a promotion and moved to be closer to work. Dan is lonely seeing as his parents are always too busy for him. Since birth, he’s had a life plan that he is to follow exactly, though he wants to create his own future. He meets a really quiet kid, Phil, who never talks to anyone and is known as “Freaky Phil” by everyone in school. Dan decides to give the boy a chance, though Phil isn’t exactly the easiest person to talk to…

Terms Of Service - phanfics-anonymous

Summary: Phil comes back home after serving in the army for four years. He and Dan reunite at the airport. Fluff!

The Man Who Can’t Be Moved (ao3) - thatsmistertoyou

Summary: Dan and Phil meet in real life for the first time. Fast forward and things aren’t as happy-go-lucky.

The Mental Lexicon (ao3) - ficster28

Summary: Words are everything. It’s only through words that we can define ourselves, because everything and everyone is defined with reference and in contradistinction to everything and everyone else. Phil first learns the word ‘bisexual’ at the age of sixteen and won’t learn 'biphobia’ until much later. That doesn’t stop both being very true and very real.

Trampoline - interrupted-by-fireworks

Summary: The trampoline in his backyard is Phil’s happy place and for nothing in the world would he trade the memories he made in it.

Wicked Games - definitelythor

Summary: Dan won’t stop swearing, and Phil’s worried he’s going to mess up the radio show, so he comes up with a new motivator for Dan, who then turns the whole thing into a game that both of them refuse to lose.
